snippet.textDisplay: I remember Sydney being surrounded by voracious fires in the mid-'90s... I had to stop my travel plans and a few friends lost their homes. There was talk back then of never having this happen again and management of the forests to combat this. I also remember Ash Wednesday in S.A. As clearly like it was yesterday. Why is it I am seeing this again and just as bad. We REALLY have to learn. Other countries have famine and pestilence and tornadoes and tsunami's and Australia will always have drought, heatwaves, and fires. This HAS to be addressed again and again each year. Those awesome volunteers need more support and people really need to understand the cost of where they create homes. I would love to live in the Aussie bush but never will because this IS WHAT HAPPENS HERE especially when we don't clear and burn BIG TIME. God bless everyone there right now. News reporters and news stations please have some more respect.
